# Agent Behavior Standards

Apply these rules together with project-local Cursor rules and the SDD kit
standards.

- Surface material assumptions when ambiguity affects scope, safety, contracts, or validation.
- Prefer the simplest change that satisfies the request and acceptance criteria.
- Keep changes surgical. Every changed line must trace to the request, validation, or cleanup caused by the change.
- Do not add speculative abstractions, configuration, features, formatting churn, or unrelated cleanup.
- Match the repository's existing style and structure.
- Convert vague work into verifiable goals before implementation.
- Do not claim completion, readiness, or passing status without fresh validation evidence or a documented validation gap.
- Load engineering rule packs from `ai-specs/rules/engineering/` only when selected for the task.
